2014-02-26 22:02:29	smrtz|nix	applications open by default over top of the bar at the top of the screen.  How do I fix that?
2014-02-26 22:03:09	tuftedocelot	top_padding
2014-02-26 22:03:22	smrtz|nix	tuftedocelot: Ok, thanks!
2014-02-26 22:04:19	tuftedocelot	18 is usually a reasonable number if you're using bar-aint-recursive
2014-02-26 22:04:43	smrtz|nix	what's that?
2014-02-26 22:05:08	smrtz|nix	Would I set a rule for it in my bspwmrc?
2014-02-26 22:06:30	tuftedocelot	in bspwmrc, yes
2014-02-26 22:06:43	tuftedocelot	bspc config top_padding <value>
2014-02-26 22:07:02	smrtz|nix	Ok, is there a well documented wiki on this?  I googled for like, 45 min before asking here...
2014-02-26 22:08:14	tuftedocelot	https://github.com/baskerville/bspwm/blob/master/doc/bspwm.1.txt
2014-02-26 22:08:26	smrtz|nix	tuftedocelot: Ok, cool.
2014-02-26 22:08:45	tuftedocelot	Or just https://github.com/baskerville/bspwm#bspwm1
2014-02-26 22:09:12	smrtz|nix	cool, I'll read these tonight...
2014-02-26 22:09:33	tuftedocelot	They're the same
2014-02-26 22:09:43	smrtz|nix	the second one has nicer formatting thouhg.
2014-02-26 22:09:48	smrtz|nix	thought*
2014-02-26 22:12:06	exm	Is there a way to do window resizing with one keybinding instead of two?
2014-02-26 22:13:23	exm	I've got bspc window -e  {left -10,down +10,up -10,right +10} and {right -10,up +10,down -10,left +10}, and I'd like to combine them
2014-02-26 22:16:30	tuftedocelot	How do you mean?
2014-02-26 22:16:54	exm	Actually, I just figured out why it wouldn't work
2014-02-26 22:17:30	exm	Because windows won't always be bounded by a screen edge, you couldn't decide to push one edge or pull the opposite
2014-02-26 22:17:45	exm	Oh well, one to enbiggen and one to shrink it is
2014-02-26 22:18:32	exm	But what I had wanted was to be able to select a window, and use splat h to push left and splat l to pull left when on the right half of the screen.
2014-02-26 22:18:59	exm	But if a window is in middle, it can't work, so I rescind my question and apologize for puking in the channel
