2014-02-27 10:03:14	dimeshake_	if i've two windows on a desktop and would like to orient them horizontally instead of vertically -- what bspc command will do that?
2014-02-27 10:07:21	tuftedocelot	Hm, if I'm visualizing this correctly, then the rotate command ought to do the trick
2014-02-27 10:08:25	dimeshake_	oh neat
2014-02-27 10:08:30	dimeshake_	this'un should do
2014-02-27 10:08:34	tuftedocelot	Try: bspc desktop -R 90
2014-02-27 10:08:48	tuftedocelot	Is that what you're looking for?
2014-02-27 10:09:05	dimeshake_	yes it is!
2014-02-27 10:09:07	dimeshake_	excellent
2014-02-27 10:09:09	dimeshake_	thanks
2014-02-27 10:09:41	tuftedocelot	No problem. I have that set to a keybind
2014-02-27 10:09:57	dimeshake_	yep, adding that now myself.
2014-02-27 10:10:08	dimeshake_	curious, what've you bound it to?
2014-02-27 10:10:12	tuftedocelot	super + r
2014-02-27 10:10:16	dimeshake_	heh also what i chose
2014-02-27 10:10:54	dimeshake_	yep, works a treat
2014-02-27 10:10:56	dimeshake_	thankya
2014-02-27 10:11:13	tuftedocelot	You're welcome!
