2014-02-27 14:31:05	earsplit	hi you still there?
2014-02-27 14:31:21	earsplit	read up on preselection
2014-02-27 14:31:36	<--	hardcore (~hardcore@s15423758.onlinehome-server.info) has quit (Ping timeout: 240 seconds)
2014-02-27 14:32:02	earsplit	pretty necessary for bspwm
2014-02-27 14:32:33	-->	hardcore (~hardcore@s15423758.onlinehome-server.info) has joined #bspwm
2014-02-27 14:32:38	earsplit	# Presel window for splitting
2014-02-27 14:32:40	earsplit	alt + ctrl + {h,j,k,l}
2014-02-27 14:32:42	earsplit	        bspc window -p {left,down,up,right}
2014-02-27 14:33:05	earsplit	or alternatively
2014-02-27 14:33:25	earsplit	flip the tree 180 degrees and move window two into the larger spot
2014-02-27 14:33:28	earsplit	there's a million ways to do that
2014-02-27 14:34:01	earsplit	bspc desktop -F vertical
2014-02-27 14:34:31	earsplit	then move the window where you want it to go, either with bspc window -s left / right
2014-02-27 14:34:43	earsplit	or with bspc window -s biggest
2014-02-27 14:34:55	earsplit	(move window to left right or move window into biggest space)
2014-02-27 14:35:42	smrtz|nix	window -s biggest?  I want that.  Thanks.
2014-02-27 14:39:42	earsplit	for some reason i've had this keybind in every WM i've ever used
2014-02-27 14:39:43	earsplit	# Move current window to largest space
2014-02-27 14:39:45	earsplit	alt + Return
2014-02-27 14:39:47	earsplit	        bspc window -s biggest
2014-02-27 14:39:50	earsplit	is that an xmonad default?
2014-02-27 14:41:09	tuftedocelot	Looks like it? http://www.haskell.org/wikiupload/b/b8/Xmbindings.png
2014-02-27 14:42:03	siwoti	earsplit: if I understand correctly preselection if for the next new window but in this case I want to move an existing window
2014-02-27 14:43:35	siwoti	I tried all your commands but somehow I never get window 1 to be below window 3 on the left
2014-02-27 14:45:49	earsplit	take your pick of methods
2014-02-27 14:46:24	earsplit	i can think of like 4 ways to do it
2014-02-27 14:46:24	earsplit	http://paste.unixhub.net/index.php/3Rny/
2014-02-27 14:46:24	earsplit	option 1
2014-02-27 14:46:24	earsplit	option 2
2014-02-27 14:46:24	earsplit	http://paste.unixhub.net/index.php/rcR/
2014-02-27 14:47:29	siwoti	ah yes I understand with the -F vertical
2014-02-27 14:47:47	earsplit	this one is with -F vertical
2014-02-27 14:47:48	earsplit	http://paste.unixhub.net/index.php/Jtd/
2014-02-27 14:48:00	earsplit	the first one was with spawning a new window in that spot using presel
2014-02-27 14:48:16	earsplit	the second one was moving an already spawned window into the preselcted space
2014-02-27 14:48:46	earsplit	my natural instinct was to use method 3
2014-02-27 14:48:56	earsplit	spawn 3 windows, preselect the first and move the window i wanted into that space
2014-02-27 14:49:30	siwoti	<earsplit> the second one was moving an already spawned window into the preselcted space
2014-02-27 14:49:37	siwoti	hwo do you do that is what I don't get
2014-02-27 14:52:21	earsplit	# Move window into presel position
2014-02-27 14:52:23	earsplit	alt + shift {a,s,d,f}
2014-02-27 14:52:26	earsplit	        bspc window -w {left,down,up,right}
2014-02-27 14:53:38	siwoti	ah thanks!
2014-02-27 14:53:48	earsplit	i dont really know what else that is useful
2014-02-27 14:54:01	earsplit	i dont quite understand how that command works
2014-02-27 14:54:14	earsplit	i just use it to move a window in to a preselected space
2014-02-27 14:54:34	earsplit	if you try to move it into a space that isn't preselected, it fucks with the tree
2014-02-27 14:55:16	smrtz|nix	earsplit: yeah, I've noticed a lot of that.  I just installed bspwm like, 3 days ago, and I'm still trying to learn how this tree thing works....
2014-02-27 14:55:56	earsplit	this is probably a safer alternative: # Move window into presel position
2014-02-27 14:55:58	earsplit	alt + shift {a,s,d,f}
2014-02-27 14:56:00	earsplit	        bspc window -w {left.manual,down.manual,up.manual,right.manual}
2014-02-27 14:56:47	earsplit	so you dont fuck with your tree
2014-02-27 15:05:33	smrtz|nix	earsplit: just tested that, it's weird, but I like it.
2014-02-27 15:05:34	smrtz|nix	thanks.
2014-02-27 15:10:27	earsplit	yeah there's a way to integrate it with the regular movement keys though
2014-02-27 15:11:02	earsplit	so alt + shift hjkl will move the window into a presel space if its available
2014-02-27 15:11:08	earsplit	otherwise it will just swap the window
2014-02-27 15:11:09	smrtz|nix	Oh? just add a modifier like Ctrl and replace asdf with hjkl?
2014-02-27 15:11:17	earsplit	nah hold on
2014-02-27 15:11:21	earsplit	lemme figure it out
2014-02-27 15:11:25	earsplit	its a little more elegant then that
2014-02-27 15:18:43	earsplit	maybe not
2014-02-27 15:18:55	smrtz|nix	 Lol.
